{
  "text": "Similar results have been observed in phase II and III studies of panitumumab. In a phase II study of 148 patients with EGFR-positive mCRC, grades 2-4 skin toxicity was associated with longer PFS (HR 0.67; 95% CI 0.50 to 0.90) and OS (HR 0.72; 95% CI 0.54 to 0.97) compared with grades 0-1 skin toxicity [CITATION_1] . In the pivotal phase III, open-label trial comparing panitumumab monotherapy with best supportive care for the treatment of mCRC, exploratory analysis revealed a trend toward longer progression-free survival (HR 0.62; 95% CI 0.44-0.88) and overall survival (HR 0.59, 95% CI 0.42-0.85) in patients with grade 2-4 skin toxicity compared with patients with grade 1 skin toxicity [CITATION_2] .",
